<Class name="BGP_Manager" id="a08f480e-0a8d-4674-9fda-dbfc55c10cfe">
    <superclass name="BGP_Object"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>Back ground processing manager class. Used to manipulate the BGP controllers.

If a new controller class is added the following steps need to be implemented to allow 
for this new class -

1) Create new BGP_Request class.
2) Call or re-implement BGP_Request methods action(), initRequest() or initRequestFromController().

	The action method is called once the controller application picks up a request once it has been persistently 
	created and the initRequest method has fired a process request.</text>
